This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an optimization algorithm for selecting a subset of training data to induce sparsity for Gaussian process regression. It also mentions the use of the marginal likelihood and variational free energy as objectives, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as Gaussian processes are a popular tool in AI for regression and classification tasks. 

The paper mentions the use of the algorithm for regression problems on discrete or continuous domains, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these sub-categories often deal with continuous data. 

Finally, the mention of hyperparameters and optimization suggests it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as this sub-category deals with the design and analysis of complex systems, which often involve optimization.
